					<td id="steps_tab_explain">
						<ul>
							<li>
								<b>Temporary folder :</b> this folder contains temporaries files used (example *.blex files). 
							</li>
							<li>
								<b>Log file :</b> this folder contains the differents actions used by current user and messages 
								(errors, informations and warnings).
							</li>
							<li>
								<b>Migrate database (V1 -> V2) :</b> when you migrate or import/export a materials database a copy is 
								created into folder 'save'. Before check this box, please make sure you have one copy because if an error 
								occurs you lost all your datas. 
							</li>
							<li>
								<b>Pycache folder :</b> this folder contains python compiled files created by Blender, if you active this box,
								'__pycache__' folders are removed. Don't worry because the folders are recreated at next execution of Blender.    
							</li>
							<li>
								<b>Archive files (zip) :</b> this folder contains all archives already used. 
							</li>
							<li>
								<b>Auto-backup files :</b> depending your current configuration (please see 'Auto-backup' section for more 
								details). You can remove all backups included inside folder 'save'. 
							</li>
							<li>
								<b>Materials preview folder :</b> you can removed all previews of materials inside 'Materials database' folder.
							</li>
						</ul>						
